                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13615877" author="nehanarkhede" created="Wed, 27 Mar 2013 23:08:05 +0000"  >&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Mirror maker shares the producer data channel and producer thread from migration tool.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Not sure what is the best place to put producer data channel and producer thread since it is relevant only to migration tool and mirror maker. So left it inside migration tool for now&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Same caveat as migration tool. If there are failures that causes producer threads to exit, the mirror maker will not shut down cleanly and will have to be killed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13616406" author="junrao" created="Thu, 28 Mar 2013 16:42:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch. +1. Just one minor comment. Should ProducerDataChannel be protected at the package level like ProducerThread?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13616421" author="nehanarkhede" created="Thu, 28 Mar 2013 17:00:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changed the visibility of ProducerDataChannel as per your suggestion. Thanks for the review!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
